title: 820-3332 - Quarter Fan
message:
I got this board with quarter fan spin.
PP5VS5 and SUS = 5V
PP3V3S5 = 3.3V
PP5VS3 = 0.54V

PMSLPS4 and S5 = 3.32V and 3.35v

any hint?

title: 820-3332 - Quarter Fan
message:
If PM_SLP_S4_L is stable 3.3V, then all S3 voltages should be present too; check that.
PM_SLP_S3_L stays low, or pulse high at least one time?

title: 820-3332 - Quarter Fan
message:
Then S0 voltages should pulse too; maybe not the CPU coils.

"all S3 voltages should be present too; check that."

What about pins 7 & 3 of U7950?
ALL_SYS_PWRGD pulses at least?
Did you try SMC bypass?
